# 1989 Seychellois presidential election

Presidential elections were held in the Seychelles in June 1989. Following a coup in 1977, the Seychelles People's Progressive Front was the sole legal party, and its leader, France-Albert Ren√©, was the only candidate in the election. He was re-elected with 96.1% of the votes on a 91.5% turnout.
